The man was found by a passerby on a sidewalk near a petrol station in Roodepoort on Sunday. JOHANNESBURG - A man was found in a pool of blood on the corner of Beyers Naude Drive and Juice Street after he was stabbed multiple times.The man was found by a passerby on a sidewalk near a petrol station on Sunday. When paramedics arrived on the scene, they discovered that the man was already dead. Local authorities are still investigating the matter.ER24'S Russel Meiring said: &quot;The man was assessed by ER24 paramedics and found to have sustained numerous stab wounds and showed no signs of life. It was evident to paramedics that the man had been dead for some time.&quot;(Edited by Zunaid Ismael)